LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 44
BY EDUCATION COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO EDUCATION; AMENDING SECTION 33-1631, IDAHO CODE, TO REVISE PRO-
3 VISIONS REGARDING REQUIREMENTS FOR HARASSMENT, INTIMIDATION AND BUL-
4 LYING INFORMATION AND PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT; AND DECLARING AN EMER-
5 GENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
6 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
7 SECTION 1. That Section 33-1631, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
8 amended to read as follows:
9 33-1631. REQUIREMENTS FOR HARASSMENT, INTIMIDATION AND BULLYING IN-
10 FORMATION AND PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT. (1) School districts and charter
11 schools shall undertake reasonable efforts to ensure that information on
12 harassment, intimidation and bullying of students is disseminated annually
13 to all school personnel, parents and students, including an affirmation
14 that school personnel are authorized and expected to intervene or facilitate
15 intervention on behalf of students facing harassment, intimidation or bul-
16 lying.
17 (2) School districts and charter schools shall provide ongoing profes-
18 sional development to build skills of all school staff members to prevent,
19 identify and respond to harassment, intimidation and bullying. The state
20 board shall promulgate rules regarding the content of the professional de-
21 velopment required by this subsection.
22 (3) District School district policies shall include:
23 (a) a A series of graduated consequences that may include, but are not
24 limited to, referral to counseling, diversion, use of juvenile spe-
25 cialty courts, restorative practices, on-site suspension and expulsion
26 for any student who commits an act of bullying, intimidation, harass-
27 ment, violence or threats of violence. Guidelines for such policies
28 will be set forth in the rules of the state board.; and
29 (b) In compliance with all federal and state laws protecting stu-
30 dent privacy, a procedure for the reporting of those incidents of
31 harassment, intimidation, and bullying that result in a student being
32 suspended from school pursuant to section 33-205, Idaho Code. The oc-
33 currence of such incidents shall be reported to the parents or legal
34 guardians of both the alleged victim and the alleged perpetrator and law
35 enforcement if the alleged conduct may violate any criminal law.
36 (4) Annually school districts shall report bullying incidents to the
37 state department of education in a format set forth in rule by the state
38 board. District policy shall designate persons to whom bullying reports are
39 to be made and a procedure for a teacher or other school employee, student,
40 parent, guardian or other person to report or otherwise provide information
41 on bullying activity.

